kennels, art studios, movies, flower shops, bed and breakfast, all over the  
place, lol everyone like it I guess, Snow and fire are a paradox, that make  
smoke, and smoke can kill, it comes from my great great grandfather, she 
was an  explorer, he was Clark of the Lewis and Clark expeditions, not 
bragging just  proud, they use to make snow fires in the snow all the time to keep 
warm,  Indians also once saw fires coming from a snow covered mountain top, 
and called  that snowfire too.
